result.execSummary:
The defendant Dylan Alan Dallmann was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.
  • Carrying Concealed Weapon. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Dylan Alan Dallmann in court with attorney Michael Jude.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered counts amended as follows:

COUNT 1:  DISORDERLY CONDUCT contrary to County Ordinance 63.01 to which the defendant entered a plea of no contest.  The Court found the defendant guilty of the amended charge and ordered the defendant to pay a forfeiture in the amount of $100.00 including costs to be paid by April 6, 2015 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

COUNT 2:  CARRYING CONCEALED WEAPON contrary to County Ordinance 63.015 to which the defendant entered a plea of no contest.  The Court found the defendant guilty of the amended charge and ordered the defendant to pay a forfeiture in the amount of $100.00 including costs to be paid by April 6, 2015 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION.
    No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with ETHAN G.
  Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Dylan Alan Dallmann in court with attorney Leah R. Thomas.  Defendant Dylan Alan Dallmann in custody.  Irene Elizabeth Parthum appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  hgj.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Protasiewicz, Branch 24.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for February 4, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
